headline: Massive Target 'flow center' to be mothballed until 2029
summary: The massive distribution center being constructed for Target Corp. at the former Green Meadow Golf Club in Hudson has stirred controversy for years, and now some are worried about the latest timeline for opening. headline: Founder of $100 million company says she quit her day job to rebuild her father’s Cape Cod chip empire—and there ‘wasn’t time’ to worry about nepotism
summary: Serial entrepreneur Nicole Bernard Dawes scaled her own multimillion-dollar brands, Late July and Nixie, after getting Cape Cod chips back on track: “I'm not my father. That was his dream and his company.”

headline: I was an antiques dealer before Gen Z helped grow our stationery sales to $50m
summary: Taymoor Atighetchi founded British stationery brand Papier in 2015 with sales set to hit $50m this year.
